    "Moreover, educators required little time to become proficient in the software according to Hutkemri and Nordin (2011), suggesting GeoGebra presents a minimal learning curve.",
    "While Doruk et al. (2013) acknowledged some interface limitations raised by teachers, on the whole extensive research supports GeoGebra as a platform with significant instructional utility.",
    "Its dynamic representations, modelling tools, and ease of use can potentially enhance teaching quality and enrich math learning experiences when integrated thoughtfully into lessons.",
